rComments: Practical lectures, although a bit fast at times. Tests are easy if you familiarize yourself with practice test and examples from hw. Everything is straightforward and I learned a lot.

I thought that she was a great teacher, especially compared to others at UIUC math.  She does go fast, but it's all straight from the book.  Tests are not necessarily easy but they are almost exactly like the practice tests, so if you know those forwards and backwards you're fine.  She is a solid second choice for Math 285 if Manfroi is full.

She is a nice lady, but hard to understand and teaches straight from the book with very little explanation.  Goes very fast in lectures, and never really pauses to give students time to understand.  Tests aren't too bad because she gives you a practice exam very similar in concepts.  Not great by any means, but not a horrible professor.
